The 2022 race for Homa Bay governor has began to take shape as Gatundu South MP Moses Kuria urged residents to support Woman Representative Gladys Wanga. “I normally see Wanga is reported in media to have initiated projects to help the people of Homa Bay. Reward Wanga by voting her to become Homa Bay governor in the next general poll,” he said. Kuria on Saturday said Homa Bay would go on record as the first county in Nyanza to have a woman governor if Wanga is elected. He spoke during a fundraiser at Odienya SDA church in Rangwe constituency, Homa Bay County,  